data.name: label18.Text
data.value:
F1 – When filtering by Set; Marks all the non-Variant Card from the Set as Owned. This works one-way only. Pressing F1 again wont mark them as Non-Owned.
F5 - Launches the Konami's DB URL of the currently selected Card. F6 - Launches the YGO Prodeck URL of the currently selected Card (if the Card's URL is available in the DB) F7 – When filtering by set; Launches the TCG Player Listing URL of the currently selected Card (if the Card's URL is available in the DB) If the Card Viewer is filtering by Master Group; This will launch a TCG Player Search Page for the currently Selected Card. F8 – Reloads the current page UI of the Card Viewer.
F9 – Add/Remove the "Star" tag on the currently selected Card. F10 – Add/Remove the "Square" tag on the currently selected Card. F11 – Add/Remove the "Triangle" tag on the currently selected Card. F12 – Add/Remove the "Circle" tag on the currently selected Card.
Arrow Controls – Moves the Cursor on the Card Viewer.
ENTER – When filtering by set; Switches the current Owned status of the currently selected Card. "`" - An alternative to the ENTER Key – this is set so a user can comfortably mark cards with their left hand while using right hand for Arrow Keys. (The ENTER Key is too close to the arrows to use both comfortably)

data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
In this mode, the specific SetCard that corresponds to the current Set is highlighted in yellow letters (So the Setcard box is easier to find)
In this mode, you can press ENTER Key to switch the owned status quickly.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value:
The currently selected Card will display the list of SetCard next to the Card Image.
SetCard Boxes backgrounds: BLACK: Not-Owned RED: Owned
Click within the box of the SetCard to switch the owned status.
There are 2 icons for Cards in the Card Viewer: STAR: All Setcards are marked as "Owned" EXCLAMATION: At least 1 Setcard is marked as "Owned" but NOT all of them.

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: While filtering by Set we can see the rest of the information to this specific SetCard. (Code, rarity and prices) In this mode clicking "TCG Listing" button will launch the Direct TCG Player listing page for this SetCard. Also worth noting that the SetCard box that corresponds to this card is highlighted in yellow. ----------------->

data.name: label10.Text
data.value:
While filtering by Master Group we can see the Card Name, Tags and Links Buttons.
In this mode clicking "TCG Listing" button will launch the TCG Player Search page for the Card. <----------------

data.name: label6.Text
data.value: -Select the Set Group that contains the desired Set -Then select the Set to display. Click "Show Selected Set" button to filter. -Filtering by Set will offers some functionalities different than filtering by Master Group.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
Use the available filter buttons on the side to filter by MasterCard Groups: [Monster Types|Spell Types|Trap Types|Card Type (All Monsters/All Spells/ All Traps)|Color| Secondary Types| Attributes]
Search By Text: This function will filter all the Cards whose name contain the text input. Good to search by Archetypes.
